{meta: artist Eddy Arnold}
{meta: writer Fanny J. Crosby and William Howard Doane}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]Safe in the arms of Jesus safe on his gentle [G7]breast
[C]There by his love o'ershaded [F]sweetly my soul shall [C]rest
[G7]Hark 'tis the voice of angels [D7]born in a song to [G7]me
[C]Over the [D7]fields of glory over the jasper [G7]sea
[C]Safe in the arms of Jesus safe on his gentle [G7]breast
[C]There by his love o'ershaded [F]sweetly my soul shall [C]rest
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G7]Jesus my heart's dear refuge Jesus has died for me
[C]Firm on the Rock of Ages [F]ever my trust shall [C]be
[G7]Here let me wait with patience [D7]wait till the night is [G7]over
[C]Wait till I see [D7]the morning break on the golden [G7]shore
[C]Safe in the arms of Jesus safe on his gentle [G7]breast
[C]There by his love o'ershaded [F]sweetly my soul shall [C]rest
{end_of_verse}
